Lifestyle Restaurants Inc said itreduced the number of Bombay Palace Restaurants inc commonshares to be received in its previously announced mergeragreement.    Under the amended deal, Lifestyle shareholders will get oneBombay share for each six instead of five Lifestyle shares.Under the amended offer, Bombay will issue about 900,000shares, currently 7.2 mln dlrs.    The amendment also increases the cash consideration to beoffered on Lifestyle's 13 pct convertible subordinateddebentures from 55 pct of the principal amount to 57.5 pct.         Reuter&#3;